1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:11,600
<i> Enriquez?</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:12,933
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

3
00:00:13,067 --> 00:00:14,600
<i>Sir, didn't you text me
last night?</i>

4
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:17,867
<i>I saw you all beat up,
so I brought you here.</i>

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:18,600
<i> Bobby!</i>

6
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:19,867
<i> Someone's looking for you.</i>

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:20,667
<i> Enriquez.</i>

8
00:00:24,267 --> 00:00:25,133
<i> Hurry up.</i>

9
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:27,067
<i>Thanks for bringing
the medicine here.</i>

10
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,800
<i>After what you did
to me last night...</i>

11
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,433
<i>You did do something?
Last night?</i>

12
00:00:30,567 --> 00:00:32,067
<i>Sir, what did my granddaughter
do to you?</i>

13
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,700
<i>Grandmother,
I didn't do anything.</i>

14
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,700
<i>Make sure you and Conde
won't do anything stupid</i>

15
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,400
<i>because the Mayor
will give you an award.</i>

16
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:40,200
<i>There's a newbie at Station 12.</i>

17
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:41,767
<i>You're the one suspected
responsible</i>

18
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,833
<i>for all the trouble
that's going on.</i>

19
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:44,467
<i> Who is that?</i>

20
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,000
<i> Sergeant Enriquez.</i>

21
00:00:46,133 --> 00:00:47,100
<i> I'm not like that.</i>

22
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:48,400
<i> What's that?</i>

23
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> Your seatbelt.</i>

24
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:52,267
<i>Well, make it clear, Sir.
You keep doing this.</i>

25
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:55,733
<i>Make sure they can't find
a loophole in me.</i>

26
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:56,800
<i> You're Bullet?</i>

27
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:57,767
<i> Here is your target.</i>

28
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:58,633
<i> You listen to me.</i>

29
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,300
<i> This job is very important.</i>

30
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:01,700
<i> Hey, you listen,</i>

31
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:04,533
<i> I never miss.</i>

32
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:21,300
Selena is a performer.

33
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:28,367
Mister, what flavor?

34
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,833
Cheese, Ube.

35
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:37,067
You know, Enriquez, in our work,
feelings shouldn't prevail.

36
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:40,300
Feelings?

37
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:41,967
I don't have feelings, Sir.

38
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,900
Emotions, Enriquez.

39
00:01:45,767 --> 00:01:49,733
Of course, in our work, it's
only natural to get pissed off.

40
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,300
Look at Garcia and me.

41
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:54,100
But it's nothing personal.

42
00:01:56,567 --> 00:01:58,733
Are you talking about yesterday,
Sir?

43
00:01:58,867 --> 00:01:59,767
That's okay.

44
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:01,500
I understand.

45
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:06,633
Besides, we all want to solve
the case, right?

46
00:02:10,567 --> 00:02:11,700
We're okay now.

47
00:02:15,233 --> 00:02:15,967
Us?

48
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,767
<i> Put your hands up!</i>

49
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:47,033
<i>That's four.
Three for me, one of you.</i>

50
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:49,900
Yes.

51
00:02:51,967 --> 00:02:52,933
Yes, yes, Sir.

52
00:02:53,067 --> 00:02:54,100
That's okay.

53
00:02:54,233 --> 00:02:55,900
That's nothing, Sir.

54
00:02:56,033 --> 00:02:57,300
Okay, Sir, I'll go first?

55
00:02:57,433 --> 00:02:58,600
I'll just go see
my grandmother.

56
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:08,567
Are you withdrawing
from the election?

57
00:03:08,933 --> 00:03:09,900
Why?

58
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,533
Okay, I understand, Anton.

59
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:20,967
Get well.

60
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:26,233
Dad, what's wrong?

61
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:30,367
Anton withdrew
from the election.

62
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:31,833
He said it's due
to health problems.

63
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:35,000
Dad, I can still change
my candidacy.

64
00:03:36,033 --> 00:03:37,667
Do you want me
to be your running mate?

65
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,833
I was the number one councilor
last elections.

66
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:44,667
Glenn, that's why many voted
for you

67
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,467
because eight councilors
were needed.

68
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:50,533
The Mayor-Vice Mayor race
is a different story.

69
00:03:50,667 --> 00:03:53,300
Del Mundo will definitely
defeat you.

70
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,133
So who do you plan
as replacement?

71
00:03:57,267 --> 00:03:59,867
If Vice Mayor Leslie Del Mundo

72
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,633
had agreed to be
my running mate,

73
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:05,767
I'd definitely have
a big lead over Victor.

74
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:09,767
Faye.

75
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:14,167
Daddy, can I not come later?

76
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:19,367
I'm still not okay
to appear in public.

77
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,400
Faye, trust me, my child,

78
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:27,567
nothing will happen to you
at that Fiesta.

79
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:33,433
We need to show the public
that our family is okay.

80
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:36,333
Okay?

81
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,100
Just for me, my daughter.

82
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,533
Please?

83
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:42,433
Okay, Daddy.

84
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:44,133
I'm just going to get dressed.

85
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,367
Thanks, my child.

86
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,367
Okay.

87
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,333
I'll just call someone.

88
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,867
Dude, grilled.

89
00:05:01,667 --> 00:05:02,367
Buddy, here.

90
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:04,100
Hey, it's Boss Tonyo.

91
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:06,233
- Hey, bossing!
- Boss!

92
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,867
- Bossing, bossing!
- Bossing, Bossing.

93
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,433
Hey.

94
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:11,867
What are you doing here?

95
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:12,867
Of course, Boss, you know.

96
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Where there's plenty of food,
we're there.

97
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,500
And of course, Boss,
when there's a Fiesta,

98
00:05:16,633 --> 00:05:17,467
we're always there.

99
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,700
You know that, of course.

100
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,367
That's a food trip.

101
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:24,033
Hey, maybe you're here to steal.

102
00:05:24,167 --> 00:05:25,133
- Oh, no, no.
- Of course not.

103
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:27,233
If you get caught,
I won't save you.

104
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:28,100
No, no, Boss.

105
00:05:28,233 --> 00:05:29,333
We won't do that.

106
00:05:29,467 --> 00:05:30,933
Good boy, Boss.

107
00:05:31,067 --> 00:05:32,000
So, how about it, Boss?

108
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,300
We'll just go there.

109
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:34,333
We'll go on a food trip first.

110
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,800
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

111
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:36,600
You better make sure.

112
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:38,767
Yes, Boss.

113
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,133
Thank you!

114
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:50,933
Mayor, Good Morning.
Happy Fiesta po.

115
00:05:51,067 --> 00:05:53,000
It's good that your family
made it.

116
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,833
Well, of course, every year,
we're here, aren't we?

117
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:57,533
Let's eat, Mayor.
We've prepared a lot.

118
00:05:57,667 --> 00:05:59,100
No thanks, later.

119
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,600
We'll just go around
with the family.

120
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:03,900
- Okay?
- Thank you.

121
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:05,967
Daddy, can I look around?

122
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,267
Okay.

123
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,567
You can.

124
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,533
The place is perfectly safe,
okay.

125
00:06:14,533 --> 00:06:16,567
- Be careful.
- Hija, be careful.

126
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:19,400
Glen.

127
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:20,200
Dad?

128
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,533
Keep an eye on her, okay?

129
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:24,300
Dad, I think a bodyguard
is enough already.

130
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,733
Faye might freak out.

131
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:27,467
She might think that we're
keeping a tight guard

132
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,967
on everything she does.

133
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:29,933
It's okay.

134
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:30,967
Just do it.

135
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,433
Keep an eye on her.

136
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:36,967
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

137
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:43,367
Mayor!

138
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:46,233
Thank you, thank you!

139
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:48,800
How much is this, Boss?

140
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:50,633
Twenty.

141
00:06:50,767 --> 00:06:52,500
Okay, it's expensive.

142
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:03,833
What's this?

143
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:04,967
Pig's blood.

144
00:07:05,433 --> 00:07:05,967
Blood?

145
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,233
She's beautiful.

146
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:13,767
Vince.

147
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,067
You might get enchanted there.
What's that?

148
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:18,667
Is this the first time you saw
the Mayor's daughter?

149
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,600
Yes.

150
00:07:19,733 --> 00:07:21,267
That's the face of my ex...

151
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,733
I've seen her on the internet,

152
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:25,333
but her beauty is different
in person.

153
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,067
Hey, Vince.

154
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:31,200
I'm warning you, that's
the Mayor's daughter

155
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,100
something might happen to you.

156
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:33,667
Bro, just chill.

157
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,400
Faye.

158
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,433
Brother!

159
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,600
Daddy made me follow you.

160
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,467
Daddy is something else.

161
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:43,867
Is it okay with you?

162
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,233
Of course, Glen Thank you.

163
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:47,367
Okay.

164
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,133
Let's go over to that side.

165
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,000
Okay.

166
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:51,467
Thank you.

167
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:52,833
Bro, just a second.

168
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:53,733
Hey Vince!

169
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:54,500
Look at that guy.
He left us behind.

170
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:55,600
It's Fiesta time...

171
00:07:55,733 --> 00:08:00,233
- Let's go on a food trip.
- There, let's try this.

172
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:01,567
What can I buy?
How much is that?

173
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:06,067
My child, hide your phone.
There's a lot of snatchers here.

174
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,500
- What?
- What did they say?

175
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:09,167
I think they're talking
about us, Dude.

176
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,900
That woman is something else.

177
00:08:11,033 --> 00:08:12,200
She's very suspicious of us.

178
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,433
Maybe she thinks rugby
is a vitamin.

179
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:16,400
I'll throw gold bars
at your house.

180
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:20,933
Thank you, my granddaughter
has a break.

181
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,533
I'm still on duty, Grandmother.

182
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,867
Chief asked us to come here.

183
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,833
We're going to receive
an award from the Mayor.

184
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:28,767
That's me and Lieutenant Conde.

185
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:31,300
Sir Tonyo? Did you two talk?
Did you see each other?

186
00:08:31,433 --> 00:08:34,333
Yes, he's just roaming around.

187
00:08:34,467 --> 00:08:35,633
And you're both okay?

188
00:08:36,133 --> 00:08:38,767
We're okay, Grandmother.
Yes, why? We just talked.

189
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:42,100
Did you talk about what happened
last night?

190
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:43,600
Grandmother,

191
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:48,300
nothing happened that's why we
have nothing to talk about.

192
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:50,067
- Hey Bobby.
- Bobby.

193
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,633
Since you're here, why don't you
join the games later?

194
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:57,467
Yes Bobby, I heard the grand
prize is a winner!

195
00:08:57,633 --> 00:08:59,600
Don't join that anymore.

196
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:03,600
Give the prize to them,
to our fellow barangay members.

197
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:04,667
Just give it to them.

198
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,367
Well, what now?

199
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,133
You heard Grandmother, right?

200
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:11,733
Too bad, I wanted to join
but you know,

201
00:09:11,867 --> 00:09:14,933
What Grandmother says,
we have to follow.

202
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:17,067
- Too bad.
- Too bad.

203
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,233
It's not bad.

204
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,200
You should follow.

205
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:20,867
If that was me, I'd join.

206
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,567
Amo!

207
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,033
Amo!

208
00:09:25,167 --> 00:09:25,867
Amo!

209
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,867
Happy Fiesta.

210
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,033
Amo is really kind,
he visited us here.

211
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,833
Thank you.

212
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:32,900
You dress like a young woman.

213
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:38,233
Happy Fiesta! Happy Fiesta!

214
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:41,000
Mayor, Happy Fiesta!

215
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:42,800
Verns.

216
00:09:42,967 --> 00:09:43,467
Yes?

217
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,800
Make a withdrawal.

218
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:47,433
We'll be needing a large amount.

219
00:09:47,567 --> 00:09:48,367
Yes, Amo.

220
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:52,567
- Thank you! Happy Fiesta!
- What? Are you okay there?

221
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:53,767
Are you okay?

222
00:09:58,233 --> 00:10:01,167
Wow...

223
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:02,867
- Yes.
- What is this?

224
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:04,733
Skin.

225
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:06,067
How much?

226
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:06,933
Fifteen.

227
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:08,900
- Okay. I'll order one.
- One.

228
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:11,667
- And then one of these.
- Okay.

229
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:24,500
Boss, are you going to buy one?

230
00:10:24,633 --> 00:10:25,433
No, Mister.

231
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:27,467
I'm just looking at something.

232
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,333
I know.

233
00:10:28,467 --> 00:10:30,433
Maybe for your child, right?

234
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:32,100
No, Mister,
I don't have a child yet!

235
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:35,033
I don't even have a wife yet.

236
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,267
I thought you already
had a child.

237
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:41,333
- This is beautiful, Mister.
- Of course.

238
00:10:41,467 --> 00:10:42,833
Lots of bubbles.

239
00:10:44,733 --> 00:10:46,767
Your toys are impressive,
Mister, aren't they?

240
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:47,533
Here's another one.

241
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:52,867
This is okay, Mister,
and this too.

242
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,300
What, this is a horn.

243
00:10:57,567 --> 00:11:01,533
Wait a minute,
Mister I can't seem to choose.

244
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,633
Vince, hey!

245
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:06,867
Let's go to the other side
to celebrate.

246
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,867
People here are so judgmental.

247
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,700
Wait a minute, Bro.

248
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:15,667
Miss, maybe I can have this.

249
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:18,167
Come on, Miss.
In the spirit of Fiesta.

250
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,367
Okay.

251
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,900
Thank you, Miss.

252
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:27,800
Bro, just a moment.

253
00:11:27,933 --> 00:11:28,533
Why?

254
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:30,267
Maybe you can give this to her.

255
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:31,200
Who?

256
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:32,900
There, to the woman, Bro.

257
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:34,467
To that woman?
The Mayor's daughter?

258
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,567
Oh my, no way.

259
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,767
Their bodyguards might mistake
me for a snatcher.

260
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,233
You really are a snatcher.

261
00:11:39,367 --> 00:11:40,533
You give it.

262
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,867
Wait, why me? He asked you
to give it. You should do it.

263
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:44,800
Come on Bro, please.

264
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:46,367
You're the most handsome among
us.

265
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:47,800
Go ahead! You can do it!

266
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:48,900
Really?

267
00:11:49,033 --> 00:11:51,133
Go ahead, just stay there.
Don't leave there, okay?

268
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,800
Okay, Bro.

269
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:53,667
Miss!

270
00:11:55,267 --> 00:11:56,300
Someone wants you to have this.

271
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:57,867
Wait! Just a moment.
I'll just give you something.

272
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,167
It's okay, Mister.

273
00:11:59,467 --> 00:12:01,167
My friend wants you
to have this.

274
00:12:01,733 --> 00:12:02,400
Who?

275
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:03,133
There.

276
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:05,567
He's gone.

277
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,533
He left but he wants you
to have this.

278
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:10,933
Tell your friend, thank you.

279
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:15,800
Good morning, Barangay folks!

280
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:19,733
Are you ready to play and win?

281
00:12:19,867 --> 00:12:20,933
Yes!

282
00:12:21,067 --> 00:12:23,467
Wait, I can't hear it!
Are you ready?

283
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,700
Yes!

284
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:28,367
And if so, we need volunteers.

285
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:32,233
Four men and four women.

286
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:36,300
Here, what you'll do is very
simple, but the prize is huge!

287
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:40,233
Three months of groceries!

288
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:42,733
So what are you waiting for?

289
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:44,400
Go to the middle!

290
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:45,967
There you go!

291
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:48,633
Come on, Let's join.
There's a prize!

292
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,367
- You guys can handle it.

293
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:54,367
Go ahead, Boss Tonyo!
- Give us the prize! Come on!

294
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:58,667
Just this once, come on!
Hey, she's joining too.

295
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,433
Hey, Sir Tonyo, joined.

296
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:01,367
That's right, sis.

297
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,300
Come on, let's join too.

298
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:04,233
If you're joining,
I'm joining too.

299
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:08,033
We're still missing one girl.

300
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:09,200
Bobby!

301
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:11,400
Bobby, Bobby will join in.
You come on and join.

302
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:14,133
Grandmother, I don't want to.

303
00:13:14,267 --> 00:13:15,533
She's joining, she's joining!

304
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:19,267
You said, Grandmother, to let
others from our barangay win?

305
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,033
No, no, you join.

306
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:20,967
Go ahead and join.

307
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,467
- No, Grandmother.
- Come on and join.

308
00:13:22,633 --> 00:13:24,900
Bobby, whatever Grandmother
says...

309
00:13:25,033 --> 00:13:26,900
- You have to follow.
- Follow.

310
00:13:27,033 --> 00:13:29,033
See? You follow.

311
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:32,200
Is everyone ready?

312
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:33,867
That's it!

313
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,333
Hello!

314
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:52,333
I can't believe you've convinced
Faye to come with us today.

315
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:53,533
Of course!

316
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,567
Whether she's ready or not.

317
00:13:58,667 --> 00:14:02,600
Well, for you, it's all about
public perception, right?

318
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:07,200
You know, what people believe
is what they see.

319
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:12,400
And right now, we're a couple
that's madly in love.

320
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:23,700
Hey!

321
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,000
Joaquin!

322
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,000
- Victor.
- Sophia!

323
00:14:27,133 --> 00:14:29,000
I didn't know you were here.

324
00:14:29,533 --> 00:14:30,667
We were just roaming around,

325
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:33,500
maybe you'd like to come
with us.

326
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:35,567
Is your husband serious, Sophia?

327
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:39,833
Well, you have to ask him,
Victor.

328
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:42,467
But it's always nice to see you.

329
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:46,267
What's your gimmick, Joaquin?

330
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,133
Why?

331
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:49,433
Do you want to show people
that we get along?

332
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:51,733
Dude, this isn't a gimmick.

333
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:54,067
Do you know I'm grateful to you?

334
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,833
I like challenges, Dude.

335
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:56,700
Do you know why?

336
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,800
In my political career,

337
00:14:58,933 --> 00:15:00,933
this is the first time
I've gotten my blood pumping,

338
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,100
would you believe?

339
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,967
Because when we were in showbiz,

340
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:09,767
you were always a worthy and
challenging opponent, remember?

341
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:14,367
I guess,
I'll take that as a compliment.

342
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,867
And, dude, to tell you the
truth.

343
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,900
This is a challenge for me

344
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:21,867
because it pushes me
for the better

345
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,667
and I just want to be a better
person right now.

346
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:28,933
Is this another pissing contest,

347
00:15:29,067 --> 00:15:32,700
gentlemen, or are you rehearsing
for a movie?

348
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,933
Leslie, how are you?

349
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:37,233
Vice Mayor Del Mundo.

350
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:39,833
Amo, Mayor.

351
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,833
How was the Fiesta celebration?

352
00:15:41,967 --> 00:15:44,200
Have you eaten a lot of food
from different houses?

353
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:46,400
Yes, I am very full.

354
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:48,900
Leslie.

355
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:49,967
Mayor.

356
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:52,100
Since you're here,

357
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:58,033
can we talk about joining forces
this coming election?

358
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:00,733
What do you think?

359
00:16:00,867 --> 00:16:02,333
And, Leslie,

360
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:05,500
you're both incumbents
running for reelection.

361
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:08,033
Wouldn't it be better if you
were from the same party?

362
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,833
That's what I'm saying.

363
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:14,367
My countrymen voted me
in as an independent.

364
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:19,267
I think, Sophia, that maybe I'd
like to keep it that way.

365
00:16:20,267 --> 00:16:22,067
But, Mayor...

366
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,567
I didn't say I wasn't looking
for an ally.

367
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:28,000
The election campaign is still
long.

368
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:29,733
We'll see, we'll see.

369
00:16:29,867 --> 00:16:31,000
Enjoy the Fiesta.

370
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:32,867
- Okay.
- Okay, okay, Leslie.

371
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Amo,

372
00:16:34,133 --> 00:16:35,667
- Sophia.
- See you around.

373
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:38,767
What now? I'll be ahead too.

374
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:42,900
After all, come election time,
I'll be ahead of you too.

375
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:44,267
Just kidding,
just kidding.

376
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,700
So, Buddy, I'll go ahead.

377
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:46,933
Happy Fiesta.

378
00:16:49,067 --> 00:16:51,033
Okay, so listen up!

379
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:56,433
What we're going to do today
is like a trip to Jerusalem.

380
00:16:56,567 --> 00:16:57,867
What's that? Similar?

381
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,267
You're right, Abdul.

382
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:04,967
The men sit in the gazebo while
blindfolded.

383
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:07,233
And when the music starts
playing,

384
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:10,733
the women spin around
while dancing.

385
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:13,033
And when the music stops

386
00:17:13,167 --> 00:17:14,767
and you're standing in front
of someone,

387
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,867
he'll be your partner
in the game

388
00:17:17,033 --> 00:17:22,033
where you can win a grocery
package for three months.

389
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:23,433
There you go!

390
00:17:23,567 --> 00:17:28,067
So don't forget, you must dance!

391
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:31,533
Whoever doesn't dance,
elbow macaroni.

392
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:32,400
Is that okay?

393
00:17:32,533 --> 00:17:33,700
What? Let's start.

394
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:35,700
Go, put on the blindfold!

395
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:41,067
And three, two, one, go!

396
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:16,833
You thought you were surprised,
didn't you?

397
00:18:16,967 --> 00:18:19,700
You know, Miss, you're
the luckiest girl here.

398
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,833
Imagine you got the most
handsome man as your partner.

399
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,033
You're disgusting.

400
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:32,267
Hi, Miss.
I'm Beteng and you are?

401
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,467
I am...

402
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:35,467
unlucky!

403
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,100
You're lucky, oh.

404
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:41,867
I know you've been dreaming
of this for a long time.

405
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,767
Okay, you can bring me home.

406
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:44,967
Hey!

407
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:46,600
You're so thick-faced,
aren't you?

408
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:48,433
You thought you are handsome.

409
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:49,200
She refuses.

410
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:59,667
Look at the opportunity,
Enriquez.

411
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:02,833
Sir.

412
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:09,767
Here it is.

413
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,733
What we're going
to do is simple.

414
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:17,600
So we're going to draw a fruit
and give it to each partner.

415
00:19:17,733 --> 00:19:23,533
And all they have to do is
squeeze it with their lips

416
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:26,333
while going around the gazebo.

417
00:19:26,467 --> 00:19:29,533
Whoever is the fastest,
they're the winner.

418
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:34,867
Yes, that's why Lee
and Peach must prepare.

419
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:38,067
And the fruit assigned
to them is...

420
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,067
Apple!

421
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,067
Apple!

422
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,767
And three, two, one...

423
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,333
Music!

424
00:19:56,100 --> 00:20:00,033
- It fell too bad.
-It's too bad.

425
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:02,533
- They're out!
- Team One is out.

426
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:05,367
Better luck next time, Ma'am.

427
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,467
And let's call the second team.

428
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:10,467
This is Bal and Apple!

429
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,900
Yes, let's applaud!

430
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:15,733
What they got is an orange!

431
00:20:15,867 --> 00:20:17,433
That's great!

432
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:20,333
And three, two, one...

433
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:21,900
Music!

434
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,767
Oh my, what a shame! Oh my, Mar!

435
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:33,800
Brad, what a shame!

436
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:38,300
And the third team,
Beteng and Abi!

437
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:39,600
Abi...

438
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:41,367
We'll win this.

439
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,667
If we lose, we were cheated.

440
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:47,267
If we win this,
we'll start a family.

441
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:51,733
We'll have groceries right away.

442
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:55,133
And what they got was a lemon.

443
00:20:55,267 --> 00:20:59,200
Well, think about the groceries
and we'll start a family.

444
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:00,967
Just don't look at me.

445
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,500
I can't do it!

446
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:11,333
I quit! You're on your own.
I'll just sell.

447
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:13,300
Does she feel she's
a disadvantage with me?

448
00:21:13,767 --> 00:21:14,767
They lose.

449
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:18,067
And of course,
let's call the last team!

450
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:23,300
Sir Tonyo and Ma'am Bobby!
Applause for that!

451
00:21:23,433 --> 00:21:26,267
Kalamansi!

452
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,400
Right, kalamansi, kalamansi!

453
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:34,167
Enriquez, if you don't want
to continue, it's okay?

454
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:37,733
Sir, why don't I want
to continue?

455
00:21:37,867 --> 00:21:40,500
Well, I'm only after
the grand prize.

456
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:41,867
Maybe it's you.

457
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:42,867
That's okay with me.

458
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,067
No problem if you don't want
to continue.

459
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,100
No, I'm only thinking about you.

460
00:21:48,133 --> 00:21:49,600
Why me?

461
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:51,533
That's okay, Sir, okay.

462
00:21:51,967 --> 00:21:53,067
That's okay?

463
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,233
Okay.

464
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:59,100
And since no one has reached
the finish line yet

465
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:02,900
when they get there,
they'll be the winner!

466
00:22:03,033 --> 00:22:06,167
So, let's start!

467
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:07,967
I'll draw, huh?

468
00:22:09,767 --> 00:22:11,433
Here we go, Kapitana, Mar.

469
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:12,233
Okay.

470
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:16,200
And what they got is...

471
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:18,567
Kalamansi!

472
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:20,967
Kalamansi!

473
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:22,133
Yes, it's Kalamansi!

474
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:23,033
Kalamansi!

475
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:23,567
That's right!

476
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:24,633
Kapitana is right!

477
00:22:24,767 --> 00:22:25,800
Give it, give it to them!

478
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:30,133
We have a winner right away!

479
00:22:37,633 --> 00:22:40,433
In three, two, one...

480
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:42,667
Go!

481
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:02,333
Go, Boss Tonyo!

482
00:23:02,467 --> 00:23:04,200
You can do it, Boss Tonyo!

483
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:07,400
Peach, is that Sir Tonyo's
girlfriend?

484
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:09,433
That's the one we saw last
night,

485
00:23:09,567 --> 00:23:11,667
the one who was assisting
him and he took her

486
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:12,933
to Tonyo's house.

487
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:14,567
That girl?

488
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:16,167
She's really strong.

489
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,700
Maybe she put Sir Tonyo
under a spell

490
00:23:18,833 --> 00:23:20,967
when she brought him home
to seduce.

491
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:23,233
Yes, she probably put him
under a spell.

492
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,600
Well, the girl is a fighter.

493
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:26,733
Don't worry.

494
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:28,833
We won't lose to her, Sis.

495
00:23:29,267 --> 00:23:29,767
That's right.

496
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:53,300
I want to give an award because
of these extraordinary people,

497
00:24:53,433 --> 00:24:56,000
our youngest Faye was saved.

498
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:57,000
Get down!

499
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,400
Sir, we've already circled
the entire area

500
00:25:00,533 --> 00:25:01,600
but we haven't found anyone.

501
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,300
It looks like the sniper
has escaped.

502
00:25:03,467 --> 00:25:05,433
Sir, please help me.

503
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:07,633
Do you know who wants
to do this to you?

504
00:25:07,767 --> 00:25:09,100
Is he connected to Sonny?

505
00:25:09,233 --> 00:25:10,300
I'm here at Sonny's house.

506
00:25:10,433 --> 00:25:11,800
I can't find the SD Card.

507
00:25:11,933 --> 00:25:13,367
You need to find it.

508
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:14,533
We're all going
to be in trouble.

509
00:25:14,667 --> 00:25:16,733
I really feel like Selena knows
something, Boss.

510
00:25:16,867 --> 00:25:18,367
We should get ahead
of that girl!

511
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:19,967
I'll send someone.
